            <abstract>Correspondence, speeches, and publications of William Mason Grosvenor
                (1835-1900), economist, journalist, and economic editor of the <title render="italic">New York Tribune,</title>
                1875-1900.</abstract>
        </did>
        <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p><!-- BIOGHIST REQUIRED -->Economist, journalist. Grosvenor was economic editor of the
               <title render="italic"> New York Tribune,</title> 1875-1900. He wrote extensively on various aspects of the American
                economy.</p>
            <p/>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
            <head>Scope and Content</head>
            <p>Correspondence, speeches, and publications of William Mason Grosvenor (1835-1900)
                including a large number of clippings of his articles and some of his books and
                pamphlets. Grosvenor also participated actively in Liberal Republican politics, and
                materials relating to his activities in Missouri and Cincinnati are included here.
                An interesting sketchbook done by Grosvenor while on a trip in the West, circa 1870,
                is also in the collection. Among the correspondents are Carl Schurz, Nelson W.
                Aldrich, James A. Garfield, Murat Halstead, Joseph R. Hawley, Horace White, and
                Whitelaw Reid.</p>
            <p/>
        </scopecontent>
